;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-1 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:25px;width:100%;\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-2\"><p>When it comes to succulents, the only thing I enjoy more than buying succulents is\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/where-to-buy-succulents\/\">choosing the pottery to plant them in.<\/a> I'm especially addicted to blue pots. My goal is to one day have two giant teal blue pots on my front porch, both filled with bright orange succulents. Sounds great right?<\/p>\n<p>But as much as I love buying pottery and planters for my succulents, it can be a challenging task to find just the perfect\u00a0one. Over the years, I've discovered a few things that are important to consider when choosing a pot, that many beginning succulent growers don't think of.<\/p>\n<p>All of these factors can make a big difference in helping your succulents thrive.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-16415\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/04\/A-guide-to-choosing-pottery-for-succulents-arrangement-of-succulents-with-oranges-and-blues.jpg\" alt=\"A guide to choosing pottery for succulents - arrangement of succulents with oranges and blues\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" data-pin-description=\"The right succulent pots will make all the difference in growing healthy succulents! Find out more in this post. You\u2019ll learn about the materials to choose, what size of pot your succulent needs and more! #succulentpots #succulentpottery #succulentgarden #succulenttips #diysucculents #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculents #succulentarrangements #succulentweddings #typeofpottery #succulentgifts #succulentplanter #succulentinspiration #succulentdecor #diyplanters #succulentsoil #succulentpartyfavors\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/04\/A-guide-to-choosing-pottery-for-succulents-arrangement-of-succulents-with-oranges-and-blues-53x80.jpg 53w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/04\/A-guide-to-choosing-pottery-for-succulents-arrangement-of-succulents-with-oranges-and-blues-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/04\/A-guide-to-choosing-pottery-for-succulents-arrangement-of-succulents-with-oranges-and-blues-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/04\/A-guide-to-choosing-pottery-for-succulents-arrangement-of-succulents-with-oranges-and-blues-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/04\/A-guide-to-choosing-pottery-for-succulents-arrangement-of-succulents-with-oranges-and-blues-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/04\/A-guide-to-choosing-pottery-for-succulents-arrangement-of-succulents-with-oranges-and-blues-585x877.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/04\/A-guide-to-choosing-pottery-for-succulents-arrangement-of-succulents-with-oranges-and-blues-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/04\/A-guide-to-choosing-pottery-for-succulents-arrangement-of-succulents-with-oranges-and-blues-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/04\/A-guide-to-choosing-pottery-for-succulents-arrangement-of-succulents-with-oranges-and-blues.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>Drainage!<\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you've read my posts on <a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/choosing-the-right-pot-for-your-succulents\/\">watering<\/a> or <a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/well-draining-soil-for-succulent-container-gardens\/\">soil<\/a>, you've likely already hear me say&#8230; choose a pot with a drainage hole! If you come away from this post learning nothing else, remember to get a pot with a drainage hole. Seriously, this will make your life so much easier, as it takes a lot of the guesswork out of<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/how-to-water-succulent-plants\/\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">watering succulents<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>To help you even further, download my <strong><span class=\"tve-leads-two-step-trigger tl-2step-trigger-43865\">free cheat sheet<\/span><\/strong> to see what it looks like when your succulents need more or less water. <span style=\"color: #7e913b;\"><span class=\"tve-leads-two-step-trigger tl-2step-trigger-43865\">Click here to grab that, it'll be super helpful.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you find a pot you absolutely love that doesn't have a drainage hole, you've still got options! You can add drainage to most containers with a<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/21CzgEa\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">diamond tip drill bit<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.<\/span><\/p>\n<div class=\"mceTemp\"><\/div>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-3\"><div id=\"attachment_7438\" style=\"width: 745px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=potterypost_susan&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fshop%2FSusanAachCeramics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored noopener\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-7438\" class=\"wp-image-7438 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/This-post-is-so-helpful-Be-sure-to-use-a-pot-with-a-drainage-hole-for-succulents.jpg\" alt=\"This post is so helpful! Be sure to use a pot with a drainage hole for succulents!\" width=\"735\" height=\"588\" data-pin-description=\"The right succulent pots will make all the difference in growing healthy succulents! Find out more in this post. You\u2019ll learn about the materials to choose, what size of pot your succulent needs and more! #succulentpots #succulentpottery #succulentgarden #succulenttips #diysucculents #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculents #succulentarrangements #succulentweddings #typeofpottery #succulentgifts #succulentplanter #succulentinspiration #succulentdecor #diyplanters #succulentsoil #succulentpartyfavors\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/This-post-is-so-helpful-Be-sure-to-use-a-pot-with-a-drainage-hole-for-succulents-500x400.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/This-post-is-so-helpful-Be-sure-to-use-a-pot-with-a-drainage-hole-for-succulents-700x560.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/This-post-is-so-helpful-Be-sure-to-use-a-pot-with-a-drainage-hole-for-succulents.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-7438\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Handmade pot by Susan Aach | <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=potterypost_susan&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fshop%2FSusanAachCeramics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">Click here to purchase from Susan's shop<\/a><\/p><\/div>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I love using<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=potterypost_susan&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fshop%2FSusanAachCeramics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Susan Aach's<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> pottery (like this one above) because she always includes large drainage holes. Use<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/1UnG2fS\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">mesh tape<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to cover the holes to keep the soil from falling out. You can also use<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/bonsaijack_bonsai_pot_drainage_mesh_screenssas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">mesh screens<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The water flows through them easily.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As you become more comfortable with watering your succulents in a pot with a drainage hole, you can branch out and try some <a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/watering-succulents-pots-without-drainage-hole\/\">pots without drainage<\/a>. But again &#8212; if you're just starting out with succulents, a drainage hole will make things much easier.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-4\"><h3>Material<\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The next consideration is the material your pot is made of. Some common pot materials include ceramic, plastic, wood, metal and glass. So which material is best? It depends on the location of your arrangement.<\/span><\/p>\n<h4>Terra Cotta or Ceramic<\/h4>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/pots-for-succulents\/?aff=2&subid=potterypost\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Terra cotta<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=potterypost_susan&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fshop%2FSusanAachCeramics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ceramic<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are both fairly breathable materials, which means they'll work well in areas that might not get a lot of air flow. In fact, I've found they work well indoors as well as outdoors.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In direct sunlight, a terra cotta or ceramic pot can heat up&#8211;which isn't ideal for succulents, but usually isn't a huge problem. Keep in mind though, that your soil will dry out more quickly if it's left in direct sun.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-7443 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/Find-out-how-to-choose-what-type-of-pot-or-planter-will-help-your-succulent-grow-best.jpg\" alt=\"Find out how to choose what type of pot or planter will help your succulent grow best!\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" data-pin-description=\"The right succulent pots will make all the difference in growing healthy succulents! Find out more in this post. You\u2019ll learn about the materials to choose, what size of pot your succulent needs and more! #succulentpots #succulentpottery #succulentgarden #succulenttips #diysucculents #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculents #succulentarrangements #succulentweddings #typeofpottery #succulentgifts #succulentplanter #succulentinspiration #succulentdecor #diyplanters #succulentsoil #succulentpartyfavors\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/Find-out-how-to-choose-what-type-of-pot-or-planter-will-help-your-succulent-grow-best-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/Find-out-how-to-choose-what-type-of-pot-or-planter-will-help-your-succulent-grow-best-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/Find-out-how-to-choose-what-type-of-pot-or-planter-will-help-your-succulent-grow-best.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The hard thing about terra cotta and ceramic pots is they can be extremely heavy. If you choose to grow in a large pot, you may find that it's difficult to move after (and maybe even before) the soil and succulents are in. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These types of pots are also quite fragile so you have to be careful not to drop them or knock them over.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-button-wrapper\"><style type=\"text\/css\">.fusion-button.button-1 {border-radius:0px;}<\/style><a class=\"fusion-button button-flat fusion-button-default-size button-default button-1 fusion-button-default-span fusion-button-default-type\" target=\"_self\" href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/pots-for-succulents\/?aff=2&subid=potterypost\"><i class=\"fa-shopping-bag fas button-icon-left\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><span class=\"fusion-button-text\">Click here to shop for terra cotta and ceramic pots online!<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:25px;width:100%;\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-5\"><h4>Plastic<\/h4>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/2X2ko95\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Plastic<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is another popular option for pots and planters. A huge advantage to plastic is that it's not as fragile as ceramic and is often a lot lighter. The downside is that it isn't as breathable as terra cotta or ceramic. It's much harder for water to evaporate in plastic pots than pots made from other materials.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But if you use a\u00a0<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/well-draining-soil-for-succulent-container-gardens\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">well-draining soil<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and have a drainage hole in your pot, this lack of breathability shouldn't be an issue. Plastic planters come in a huge variety of colors and shapes which makes them really fun to shop for.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/2X2ko95\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-7752\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/See-the-best-way-to-root-cactus-pads-to-grow-new-plants.jpg\" alt=\"See the best way to root cactus pads to grow new plants!\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/See-the-best-way-to-root-cactus-pads-to-grow-new-plants-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/See-the-best-way-to-root-cactus-pads-to-grow-new-plants-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/See-the-best-way-to-root-cactus-pads-to-grow-new-plants.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h4>Wood<\/h4>\n<p>If you're looking for an unusual way to plant your succulents, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=potterypost_wood&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fsearch%2Fhome-and-living%2Foutdoor-and-garden%2Fplanters-and-pots%3Fq%3Dwood%2Bplanter\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">wood\u00a0<\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\u00a0is a really interesting option. I love the<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/diy-driftwood-planter-succulents\/\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">driftwood planter<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> I made last summer. It's much more eye-catching than your typical pot or planter.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Plus, wood is helpful for succulents that sit in direct sun or hot environments because it stays cool and retains water.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-7435 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/See-how-to-choose-the-best-container-for-your-succulents-including-why-wood-can-be-good-and-bad.jpg\" alt=\"See how to choose the best container for your succulents -- including why wood can be good and bad\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" data-pin-description=\"The right succulent pots will make all the difference in growing healthy succulents! Find out more in this post. You\u2019ll learn about the materials to choose, what size of pot your succulent needs and more! #succulentpots #succulentpottery #succulentgarden #succulenttips #diysucculents #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculents #succulentarrangements #succulentweddings #typeofpottery #succulentgifts #succulentplanter #succulentinspiration #succulentdecor #diyplanters #succulentsoil #succulentpartyfavors\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/See-how-to-choose-the-best-container-for-your-succulents-including-why-wood-can-be-good-and-bad-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/See-how-to-choose-the-best-container-for-your-succulents-including-why-wood-can-be-good-and-bad-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/See-how-to-choose-the-best-container-for-your-succulents-including-why-wood-can-be-good-and-bad.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">On the other hand, if you're planting in an area with less sunlight and airflow you may find that wood can easily rot or keep your soil wet for too long. The wood may also break down over time, or split from being watered. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For all these reasons, wood may not last as long as some other materials for pots. But if you choose the right spot for it, wood can look really beautiful!\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-6\"><h4>Metal<\/h4>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=potterypost_metal&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fsearch%2Fhome-and-living%2Foutdoor-and-garden%2Fplanters-and-pots%3Fq%3Dmetal%2Bplanter\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Metal<\/a> is typically not a great long term choice for planting succulents. You can use it&#8211;but be aware that it changes temperatures quickly, which can cause the soil to heat up too much.<\/p>\n<p>Also, unless you use a metal pot that's specifically designed for planting, it will eventually rust, which isn't healthy for succulents. If you decide to go with a metal container, it's best to plan on moving your succulents to a new container after a while.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/lookingsharpcactus.com\/collections\/hanging-gardens\/products\/modern-metal-address-planter-gives-curb-appeal-metal-address-sign-vertical-garden-rustic-metal-address-plaque-metal-address-numbers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-22638\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/metal-address-planter-with-succulents.jpg\" alt=\"metal address planter with succulents\" width=\"735\" height=\"1103\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/metal-address-planter-with-succulents-53x80.jpg 53w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/metal-address-planter-with-succulents-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/metal-address-planter-with-succulents-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/metal-address-planter-with-succulents-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/metal-address-planter-with-succulents-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/metal-address-planter-with-succulents-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/metal-address-planter-with-succulents-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/metal-address-planter-with-succulents-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/metal-address-planter-with-succulents.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h4>Glass<\/h4>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There's no question that <a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/1WQI5dd\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">glass<\/a> is a beautiful material to plant your succulents in. However, glass containers usually lack drainage holes (although the\u00a0<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=potterypost_winebottle&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fshop%2Flookingsharpcactus%3Fsection_id%3D17978197\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">wine bottle planter<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> below has one!).<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-7476\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/05\/Fill-your-wine-bottle-planter-with-a-variety-of-succulents-for-a-unique-look.jpg\" alt=\"Fill your wine bottle planter with a variety of succulents for a unique look\" width=\"585\" height=\"390\" data-pin-description=\"The right succulent pots will make all the difference in growing healthy succulents! Find out more in this post. You\u2019ll learn about the materials to choose, what size of pot your succulent needs and more! #succulentpots #succulentpottery #succulentgarden #succulenttips #diysucculents #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculents #succulentarrangements #succulentweddings #typeofpottery #succulentgifts #succulentplanter #succulentinspiration #succulentdecor #diyplanters #succulentsoil #succulentpartyfavors\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/05\/Fill-your-wine-bottle-planter-with-a-variety-of-succulents-for-a-unique-look-500x333.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/05\/Fill-your-wine-bottle-planter-with-a-variety-of-succulents-for-a-unique-look-700x467.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/05\/Fill-your-wine-bottle-planter-with-a-variety-of-succulents-for-a-unique-look.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 585px) 100vw, 585px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Besides the drainage issue, glass is also not very breathable, which means your soil will have a hard time drying out&#8211;unless your container has a\u00a0<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/1WQI5dd\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">wide opening<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and allows for a lot of airflow.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>Glass also gets dirty easily, and has a tendency to collect hard water deposits. And of course, it's also quite breakable, so you have to be careful with where you place your arrangements&#8211;especially if, like me, you've got little ones running around your house!<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-7\"><h3>Colors and Textures<\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now that you have a good idea of what materials might work best for your succulent planter, the fun really begins! You can take two different approaches to choosing a planter at this point&#8211;choose your pot's color and texture based on the succulents you're working with, or pick your succulents based on the pot you want to use.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cindy Davison of<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/TheSucculentPerch\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Succulent Perch<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is an expert when it comes to pairing pots and succulents. She puts a lot of thought into choosing succulents whose natural colors will mimic or complement the pot she uses.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this arrangement, for example, she's filled the pot with succulents that are similar in color and shape to the design on the pot. This helps the arrangement look unified and visually appealing.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-7441 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/This-arrangement-is-stunning-and-the-post-about-choosing-pottery-is-so-helpful.jpg\" alt=\"This arrangement is stunning and the post about choosing pottery is so helpful!\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" data-pin-description=\"The right succulent pots will make all the difference in growing healthy succulents! Find out more in this post. You\u2019ll learn about the materials to choose, what size of pot your succulent needs and more! #succulentpots #succulentpottery #succulentgarden #succulenttips #diysucculents #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculents #succulentarrangements #succulentweddings #typeofpottery #succulentgifts #succulentplanter #succulentinspiration #succulentdecor #diyplanters #succulentsoil #succulentpartyfavors\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/This-arrangement-is-stunning-and-the-post-about-choosing-pottery-is-so-helpful-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/This-arrangement-is-stunning-and-the-post-about-choosing-pottery-is-so-helpful-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/This-arrangement-is-stunning-and-the-post-about-choosing-pottery-is-so-helpful.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All these choices can get a little overwhelming, I know! If you can't decide what to plant your succulents in, or if you're having a hard time finding just the right pot, a great option is just to fall back on\u00a0<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/terracotta-standard-clay-pot-w-drainage-hole-multiple-sizes\/?aff=2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">basic terra cotta pots<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> or\u00a0<\/span><a href=\"http:\/\/amzn.to\/2FeXxft\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">simple white pottery<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It seems every succulent looks great in one of these and their simplicity helps keep the focus on the succulent.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I've put together a list of some of\u00a0<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=potterypost_favorite&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fpeople%2Fcameracassidy%2Ffavorites%2Ffavorite-pottery%3Fref%3Dfavs_index_12\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">my favorite pottery on Etsy<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> that works well with succulents. You'll find several from\u00a0<\/span><a href=\"http:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=potterypost_susan&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fshop%2FSusanAachCeramics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Susan Aach,<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> who is an incredible ceramic artist and always keeps succulents in mind when she creates her unique pieces. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The arrangement below was created by Cindy Davison of\u00a0<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/TheSucculentPerch\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Succulent Perch<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in a Susan Aach pot.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-7442 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/Find-out-how-to-use-texture-and-color-when-selecting-pottery-for-succulents.jpg\" alt=\"Find out how to use texture and color when selecting pottery for succulents\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" data-pin-description=\"The right succulent pots will make all the difference in growing healthy succulents! Find out more in this post. You\u2019ll learn about the materials to choose, what size of pot your succulent needs and more! #succulentpots #succulentpottery #succulentgarden #succulenttips #diysucculents #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculents #succulentarrangements #succulentweddings #typeofpottery #succulentgifts #succulentplanter #succulentinspiration #succulentdecor #diyplanters #succulentsoil #succulentpartyfavors\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/Find-out-how-to-use-texture-and-color-when-selecting-pottery-for-succulents-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/Find-out-how-to-use-texture-and-color-when-selecting-pottery-for-succulents-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/Find-out-how-to-use-texture-and-color-when-selecting-pottery-for-succulents.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-8\"><h3>Size considerations<\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It can often be hard to tell what size of pot you need for your succulents and arrangements. As a general rule, I recommend leaving about a half-inch of space between your succulents and the edge of the pot, so they'll have a little room to spread and grow.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Too much space can actually prevent a succulent from growing much larger, because the roots spread out before the succulent has time to catch up. If you buy a\u00a0<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/wholesale-2in-pots\/?aff=2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">two-inch<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\u00a0succulent<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, a\u00a0<\/span><a href=\"http:\/\/amzn.to\/2FfoHmo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2.5 inch pot<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is generally a good choice if you're planting it by itself.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you're combining a lot of succulents in your arrangement, you'll want to leave a little space around each of them, so they'll have some room to spread out. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A tightly packed arrangement like the one below will look beautiful as soon as it's finished and it generally prevent the succulents from growing as much.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-7432 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/Find-out-how-to-choose-the-best-pot-for-your-succulents.jpg\" alt=\"Find out how to choose the best pot for your succulents\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" data-pin-description=\"The right succulent pots will make all the difference in growing healthy succulents! Find out more in this post. You\u2019ll learn about the materials to choose, what size of pot your succulent needs and more! #succulentpots #succulentpottery #succulentgarden #succulenttips #diysucculents #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculents #succulentarrangements #succulentweddings #typeofpottery #succulentgifts #succulentplanter #succulentinspiration #succulentdecor #diyplanters #succulentsoil #succulentpartyfavors\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/Find-out-how-to-choose-the-best-pot-for-your-succulents-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/Find-out-how-to-choose-the-best-pot-for-your-succulents-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/Find-out-how-to-choose-the-best-pot-for-your-succulents.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you want your succulents to get larger and spread, give them a little &#8220;breathing room&#8221; to allow for new growth. Usually about 1\/2&#8243; to 1&#8243; is ideal.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You should now feel more equipped to purchase a new pot for your succulents. While there are a lot of things to consider when choosing a pot, it's still a really fun part of growing succulents.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once you've selected the right container, it's time to start potting! Check out my<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/how-to-plant-a-succulent\/\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">post on potting succulents<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> for a step-by-step tutorial.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>And don't forget to download my <strong><span class=\"tve-leads-two-step-trigger tl-2step-trigger-43865\">free cheat sheet<\/span><\/strong> to see what it looks like when your succulents need more or less water. <span style=\"color: #7e913b;\"><span class=\"tve-leads-two-step-trigger tl-2step-trigger-43865\">Click here to grab that, it'll be super helpful.<\